⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Ganondorf
node ZEL · ZEL · ⟦Ganondorf:ZEL:950583⟧

WHO   — Ganondorf — the Demon King
WHAT  — The great antagonist of the legend — bearer of the Triforce of Power, the conqueror who would seize the Sacred Realm and rule Hyrule; a mortal man of monstrous ambition who transforms into the beast Ganon.
WHERE — ZEL · The Legend of Zelda  Framework inputs: The Legend of Zelda (the saga entire)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because power is the only thing he has ever worshipped; because the desert that bore him knows famine and he would never kneel to it; because the curse of Demise's hatred runs in him — yet the wanting is his own, and he reaches for the relic life after life because he cannot stop reaching.
HOW   — By the sword and the conjured fire, by dark sorcery and the Triforce in his fist; by armies and deception and the patient siege of an age — and, when the man is not enough, by the tusks and bulk of the boar-beast he becomes.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the hunger that returns — born of the desert, crowned in shadow, the man who would be a god and the beast that would devour the world.

